Looking for a few actors to star in a Murder Mystery evening at a venue on the 25th October (Woodbridge, IP12 )

Timings are usually 6:00pm for a read through then start improv acting from 7:30pm to around 22:30pm.

If you are interested and have improv experience please email us at enquiries@wearethedrama.co.uk

Actors will be paid £60 on the evening and will be provided a complimentary two course meal

Thank you!

items.text:
# CASTING CALL - COMMERCIAL

Casting for a short commercial film centred on an elderly woman, whose quiet morning is disrupted by noisy neighbours - until an unexpected connection softens her day.

**This is an UNPAID job.**

*Disclaimer: All members of the cast and crew are working on the project voluntarily. This project acts as a kick-starter portfolio piece for a production studio start-up. The project is being created "pro bono" for a local family-owned bakery.*

CASTING FOR:

**ANNE (Female, elderly) –** A retired woman living alone. Sharp-witted, independent, and easily irritated, but with a softer, more vulnerable side that reveals itself in quiet moments. Requires strong emotional range and the ability to convey inner life through subtle expressions, silence, and physicality.

SUPPORTING ROLES:

**WIFE (30s–40s) **– Warm, polite, and slightly apologetic, she tries to balance being a good neighbour with managing a chaotic household.

**HUSBAND (30s–40s)** – Friendly but firm. Protective of his family while maintaining neighbourly respect.

**VOICE OF ELISA (60s–80s)** – Anne’s long-time friend. Comforting and familiar, with a touch of humour and warmth. 

**(Voiceover role only.)**

NOTES:

The film relies heavily on atmosphere, natural performances, and subtle character work. Not dialogue-heavy. Actors must be comfortable with close-up, quiet acting, and emotional nuance. We welcome applications from ALL BACKGROUNDS and LEVELS OF EXPERIENCE, and encourage older actors to apply for the lead role.

📍 Location: Bournemouth, Christchurch, and Poole area, exact TBC
 📅 Planned Shoot Dates: 1st and 2nd of November (Saturday, Sunday, subject to change)
 💰 Compensation: Unpaid / Expenses covered on a negotiation basis.

👉 To Apply: Please send your headshot, CV, and showreel (if available) to

**almasi.d@fetchkedigital.com **
[Subject line: “Toasts and Scones – Casting Application”]

or apply via the Backstage listing:

[https://www.backstage.com/casting/toasts-and-scones-start-up-commercial-3019207/](https://www.backstage.com/casting/toasts-and-scones-start-up-commercial-3019207/)

message.text:
Two auditions. Two jobs.
One retreat that changed everything.

Maryam joined our 12-day intensive at @bodlondebstudio and came away with the tools (and the confidence) to step back into acting - stronger than ever.

We bloomin love working with @manjam_ali - her readiness to show up and move into the discomfort knowing it'll be worth it in the end is admirable and very exciting.

🎥 Hear her story in her own words

#ActorTraining #BothFeet #bodlondebretreat #ActingRetreat #DoNotSuffer #Meisner #MeisnerTechnique

🎄 CHRISTMAS ELF CASTING – 2025 GROTTO CONTRACT 🎄

(PLEASE BE AWARE WE ARE CASTING FOR MULTIPLE VENUES SO READ CAREFULLY & APPLY ACCORDINGLY) 

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in Redfield – and we’re on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

📍 Location: Redfield’s Lane, Fleet, Hampshire, GU52 0AB
📆 Contract: November – December 2025
💸 Rate: £15 per hour — PAY & A HALF on Christmas Eve

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children.

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

• Full availability during weekends and key dates in November/December

• We are ideally looking for team members available for a minimum of 2 shifts per week

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

✅ Shift Dates & Times

• Sat, Nov 22 – 9:30 AM to 5:00 PM

• Sun, Nov 23 – 9:30 AM to 4:00 PM

items.text:
Casting Call

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-35 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 14th of October day time and salary will be £25 for the actor after filming, plus if actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com

+++ Kompars:innen gesucht für Debüt-Kinofilm „DIE MATRIARCHIN“ (AT) von Alison Kuhn +++

📆 14.10.2025 in Berlin

🏙 Motiv: Fußgängerzone – Schüler:innen auf dem Weg nach Hause

💶 Tagesgage: 80€ bis maximal 6h (+45min Pause)

Wir suchen noch junge Komparserie wohnhaft in Berlin im Alter von 18-21 Jahren! Zeitlich voraussichtlich 8 bis 13:00 Uhr!

Inhalt: Die 17-jährige Kim muss sich ihre Plattenbauwohnung an der deutschen Ostsee nicht nur mit ihrer vietnamesischen Mutter und ihrem kleinen Bruder Bao teilen, sondern auch mit jeder Menge wildfremden Vietnames:innen. Die Mutter betreibt in ihrem kleinen Brautmodeladen eine Agentur für illegale Schleusungen aus Vietnam nach Europa. Kim möchte mit allen Mitteln ihrer Mutter gefallen und eines Tages die Agentur übernehmen. Als sich endlich eine Chance ergibt, wird sie sich schnell bewusst, was das wirklich für sie bedeutet.

Es ist keine Vorerfahrung nötig! 🎬

Meldet euch mit KOMPARSERIE BERLIN im Betreff, Fotos von euch an:

📩 diematriarchin.extras@gmail.com

items.text:
Hello folks, my Film And Video Production students decided to begin a very ambitious project - Feature Film! Those of you who work in the industry already know how much time, effort and money it take to do a good movie, for those of you who don't know I can tell you - a lot! If you like to help them on their journey, please take a time to read their message below and if you decide to help them, please follow the link to their GoFundMe page. I've seen them in action and I've read the script, this project worth to be filmed!                                                                                                                                         

What happens when film students try to wrangle Greek Gods on a student budget?

Hey Calgary film fam, 

We're a group of SAIT film students in our final semester, and we've taken on our biggest project yet : Prometheion - a student-led feature film inspired by Greek mythology, with a bonus BTS to show the beautiful chaos making it. 

We're pouring in long day and nights, all our are creativity, and yes... way too much craft table pizza. But to really bring this story to life, we could use some extra support for wardrobe, props, locations, and keeping our crew alive through it all. 

Here's our GoFundMe : https://www.gofundme.com/f/prometheion-student-feature-film?attribution_id=sl:0597d4f7-f1e5-4ff2-86ce-2da6a9373dd2&lang=en_CA&ts=1758595706 

 Every bit helps us make this film with the ambition it deserves, and we'd be so grateful if you can contribute or share. 

 Thanks for helping us light the fire of Prometheion!

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc)

Summary: Set in the backroom of a dive bar. A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer. Black African, 25-35, Nigerian accent, 5’6”+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £500 for 20 hours (rehearsals & shoot).

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg, powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours.

You will need professional experience playing roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com

🎄 CHRISTMAS ELF CASTING – 2025 GROTTO CONTRACT 🎄

(PLEASE BE AWARE WE ARE CASTING FOR MULTIPLE VENUES SO READ CAREFULLY & APPLY ACCORDINGLY) 

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in Barton Grange – and we’re on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

📍 Location: Barton Grange, Brock, Preston, PR3 0BT
📆 Contract: November – December 2025
💸 Rate: £15 per hour — DOUBLE PAY on Christmas Eve

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside Mother Christmas in a beautifully themed setting.

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

• Full availability during weekends and key dates in November/December

• We are ideally looking for team members available for a minimum of 3–5 shifts per week

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

items.text:
🎬 **Szukasz klimatycznej przestrzeni do zdjęć filmowych?**
Warszawskie Muzeum Komputerów i Gier wraz z pasażem Warszawskiej Giełdy Elektronicznej to wyjątkowe miejsce o surowym, autentycznym charakterze.

👉 Betonowe podziemia, korytarze pełne nostalgi, retro sprzęt komputerowy i konsole – wszystko to tworzy niepowtarzalny klimat lat 80/90

📍 Lokalizacja: centrum Warszawy Al.Niepodległości 208b
🤝 Jesteśmy otwarci na kooperację z filmowcami i ekipami produkcyjnymi

Jeśli szukacie unikalnej scenografii do filmu, teledysku czy reklamy – zapraszamy do kontaktu!

tytus@wmkig.pl

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - Concert Attendees for *****SHOTGUN***

We’re looking for enthusiastic people to be part of the audience in our upcoming project ***SHOTGUN*** - a new film currently in production.

**Details:**
* **Role:** Concert Attendees (background)

* **Date:** **Saturday, 4th October**

* **Commitment:** 1 full day

* **Location:** TBC (in Auckland - details provided upon confirmation)

* **Payment:** This is an unpaid role.

This is a volunteer opportunity, but a great chance to experience being on set, collaborate with a passionate team, and bring a live concert scene to life on screen. We’d also love to keep you in mind for future projects with us.

**What we’re looking for:**
* Energetic, expressive people

* No acting experience needed - just enthusiasm and commitment for the day

**How to apply:**
 If you’re keen, please email us at lazybonesfilms@gmail.com with your:
* Name and contact details

* A recent photo (so we know who’s who on the day)

For more details about ‘SHOTGUN’: [https://www.thearts.co.nz/boosted/projects/shotgun](https://www.thearts.co.nz/boosted/projects/shotgun) 

We can’t wait to have you join us for this shoot and to make something special together.
* *Lazy Bones Films*

items.text:
Hello all! We’re hosting a very exciting industry workshop under Mimic Theatre Company With special thanks to Beam Hertford and #artsineastherts . 

Mimic Theatre Company presents: “Connect, Create & Collaborate” - A Collective Storytelling and Networking Workshop with a playground of creativity for actors, writers, producers and directors!

Connect, Create & Collaborate invites creatives to explore new ideas, develop existing projects and collaborate in a safe, supportive space.

Participants will have the opportunity to meet fellow creatives, enjoy prompts for creativity in the form of tool props and cards, improvisation and writing time, as well as receive support, advice and crucial feedback from the group. 

Bring your dreams, goals and imagination, it’s about experimenting and meeting people. 

To book your space, feel free to drop me a message or email kim@mimictheatre.co.uk. There are limited spaces available so if you’re keen to join don’t wait :)

items.text:
Acting & Storytelling Improv Workshop with Arek Ziętek

This is not your usual workshop. This is a rare chance to learn from Arek Ziętek, a Warsaw theater legend who has worked with Keith Johnstone, the father of modern improvisation.

Together, we dive deep into acting, storytelling, and improvisational theater in a way that pushes you to grow, connect, and create.

👉 Important: This is not an open event. In order to join, prior experience in acting or improv and a confident level of English is required. We’re keeping this group selective to ensure high quality, intensity, and growth for every participant.

Why join?

✨ Learn from one of Poland’s most respected improv acting teachers.
✨ Develop storytelling and performance techniques that translate to stage, film, and beyond.
✨ Work in English, one of the very few opportunities in Warsaw to grow artistically in an international setting.
✨ Build deep connections with like-minded actors and creators.

Schedule & Pricing

📆 Starting: Tuesday, October 7th
⏰ 7:00 PM
📍 Location: Atlas Tower - al. jerozolimskie 123a (Warsaw)

🎟️ Limited Packages:

First 5 applicants: 300 PLN (for full 6-week course)

Next 5 spots: 350 PLN

If more than 10 apply, a second group will be opened, but no guarantees.

🔗 Apply now through the link below. Spots will not last, once the first 5 tickets are gone, the price increases.

https://forms.gle/JguLesA9U2uf31BE7

This is your invitation to step into a smaller, more demanding circle of actors who take their craft to the next level.

📽️Projekt: Krótki, lekko surrealistyczny film, czarno - biały o aniele w połączeniu że stylem inspirowanym filmografią Wima Wendersa oraz Krzysztofa Kieślowskiego 

📅Data: jeden weekend w październiku, szczegóły do ustalenia 

📍Lokacja: Kraków oraz Skawina

💰Zapłata: 400 zł za dzień (łącznie 800 zł) + koszty za podróż 

Kogo szukamy:

Szukamy młodej (20-30 lat) jasnowłosej dziewczyny pełnej pozytywnej energii i charyzmy.  Otwartej na świat i lubiącej pracować z ludźmi

Wymagania:

- nauczenie się scenariusza

- brak widocznych tatuaży

Co odesłać 

- wizytówkę aktorską

- zdjęcia ( 1 full-body oraz 1 close-up) i/lub profil na social mediach

Zgłoszenia:

Proszę o odesłanie materiałów na maila: ignacyfialek@gmail.com 

Deadline: 3 października

Hello Actors and Directors!

My name is Morgan. I’m the Founder and Creative Producer of Tricky Ink Productions in the Bay Area. 

I am in the process of updating and reorganizing my ACTOR DATABASE. I have over 200 people currently, and I’m looking to expand. 

ACTORS: If you’d like to be added, please email me your headshot, age range, and location.

DIRECTORS: If you’re looking to cast your next project, reach out and I’ll send you details about my services. 

[Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com](mailto:Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com)

(Please don’t DM me)

BSou Repertory Theater Company is holding an open casting call for African-American actors.

DARLENE - African-American, 45-55. 5’4-5’9. A dedicated mother of four teenagers who works hard and dreams of her children attending medical school.

DARIUS - African-American, 25-35, 5’9" to 6’2". He is a lawyer aspiring to become a Supreme Court judge. He is attractive and charming. Helps the community by doing pro bono work.

JENNIFER - African-American, 19-25, 5’4-5’9. Smart, dedicated student, good daughter, great sense of humor, wants to make her mother proud. 

TERESA - African-American, 40-55, 5’5-5’10. Teresa’s next-door neighbor and best friend. She's always involved in the family business.

FRANK - African-American, 45-55.  5’9 to 6’2. A successful, self-made mechanical engineer who is smart, romantic, and in love with his next-door neighbor, who is involved with someone else.

Applicants should send their headshot and resumé to: productioncastingnyc1@gmail.com

items.text:
PIGE MED PROTESE SØGES TIL KORTFILM - (LØNNET) -ÅRHUS

Til kortfilmen “Dukkebarn” søger vi en pige med en ben protese eller arm protese til rollen som AURA. 

Lidt om filmen: 
“Dukkebarn udforsker den skrøbelige grænse mellem fantasi og virkelighed gennem øjnene på Aura. Hendes fascination til dukker bliver en måde at bearbejde hendes egen smertelige virkelighed og hendes forhold til sin krop. Gennem leg, skabelse og destruktion konfronteres hun med sine dybeste frugter og længsler. 

Alder: I mellem 6-12 år. 

Vi filmer i Århus d. 16-18 Januar 2026. Jobbet vil være lønnet, samt forplejning og transport. Søg gerne lige meget hvor i landet du bor. Vi ser gerne så mange som muligt;) 

Skriv til @Rirh.prod@gmail.com med emnet “CASTING -DUKKEBARN”. Skrive gerne lidt om dig selv, samt er billede og evt erfaring. 

Hvis du er gået videre til casting, eller fået rollen vil du få svar inden 10 Januar. 

Jeg glæder mig til at høre fra jer. 

Mvh Rebecca Renner Hansen - Dukkebarn film

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambitiøse og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en række skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske fætter hjælper ham med at flytte, må han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud – men om at turde definere sine egne grænser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke særlig bemærkelsesværdig
* har svært ved at sætte grænser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 år
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* KØN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ulønnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail på sara774g@gmail.som med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi glæder os til at høre fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

Hej alle sammen

Jeg søger en mandlig model til en kampagnevideo for vores rygsæk-brand. Der er ingen replikker, da videoen får musik og effekter som lydside, så det handler mest om tilstedeværelse og udtryk foran kameraet.

Optagelserne foregår i Århus. Projektet er på frivillig basis, men du får naturligvis det færdige materiale, som du også kan bruge til din egen portfolio.

Hvis det lyder som noget for dig, så kontakt mig over e-mail: Carlsjensen@icloud.com

På forhånd tak
Carl Schmidt Jensen

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I’m the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called “Beginnings” and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan’s life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
— learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by — but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN – VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th – 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you’d like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Naïve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him — learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan’s father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won’t make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can’t help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone’s submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

items.text:
📣 Casting Call – Vancouver 🎬
We’re filming a volunteer-based music video Not Close (non-union). Meals and credit provided.

✨ Andy (Lead, Female, 20–35) – A young woman juggling work and life, quietly resilient yet vulnerable.
🗓️ Shoots: Oct 11 & 12

✨ The Kid (Supporting, any gender, 4–10) – Sweet, energetic, and curious. The heart of the reunion.
🗓️ Shoots: Oct 12

✨ The Boss (Supporting, Male or Female, 30–60) – Stern, short-tempered, represents the grind Andy is stuck in.
🗓️ Shoots: Oct 11

Synopsis:
Not Close tells the story of Andy, a young woman pushing through the daily grind, unanswered calls, and isolation — until a heartfelt reunion with her child brings light back into her world.

📩 To submit: send headshot + resume (demo reel if available) to valerie.film.prod@gmail.com
Subject line: Not Close – [Role]

items.text:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss’s unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the “Worst Cities in Canada” list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it’s up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill’s assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5’2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she’s having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a “noncompetitive and ineffectual environment” would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she’s found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She’s annoyed she was moved onto Hannah’s task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She’s not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin’ Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a “Greybeard” or municipal government. He’s been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He’s incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a “healthy dose” of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won’t let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He’s given Hannah six months to show what she’s made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it’s not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a “cool” youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad’s respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord “Conspiracy Guy” 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who’s stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded “truth warrior” who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his “auditing” police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He’s paranoid, he’s ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he’s very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for “invading his privacy” and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ”spy drone”, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his “truth warrior” life wasn’t wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - “Oshawa”, but is legally required to let the task force know he’s not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he’s the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah’s communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it’ll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he’s been wearing it for 50 years. 

***About Character:**** *A local Oshawa “Shwallywood legend” that has had hundreds of TV and Movie productions use his driveway. A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares “Forrest Gumpian” stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. Obviously no one believes him, which makes him sad. He just just excited to have someone to talk to.

***CHARACTER****:*  Clara “Newswoman”

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***40’s

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Mid-40s, attractive but not delicate, with a confident, professional presence. Simple hair, and a face showing experience rather than youth. Blazer, smart blouse, tailored slacks. Carries a small microphone with the channel logo, Minimal jewelry. 

***About Character: ***Field reporter for a Durham Region news channel. Polished but practical, someone who can run to a chaotic scene without ruining her outfit. Clara is on-site at the Oshawa tourism task force’s Hollywood Tour location, where a body has been discovered. She delivers the story with gravity despite the absurdity of the situation. 

***CHARACTER****:* Chris

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Medium build, white, dark hair. Nerdy, glasses, thrifted clothes or ones he picked up at Costco

***About Character: ***full-time software engineer but would rather talk about his many hobbies and interests like the golden age of cinema, Napoleon, his tropical fish tank, pickleball league and making his girlfriend Julia happy. Chris saw an online ad for the Shwallywood Tour and immediately booked it as he had been looking for a way to propose to his girlfriend, Julia, for months. On the day of, Chris does not immediately react when the tour seems to be taking much longer than anticipated to get to Parkwood as he is a calm and patient person. He only becomes upset when he sees his girlfriend Julia is disappointed in the lackluster activities of the day.

***CHARACTER****:*  Julia

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thin frame, blonde or dark brown hair, A little nerdy, soft goth. 

***About Character: ***Works as a dental assistant. She realized she had a passion for teeth when she did a work placement as a mortician in high school. Julia has been taken on the Shwallywood tour by Chris, to celebrate their anniversary. She initially had very little interest, but Chris insisted on bringing her because she’s a movie buff. The tour is off to a rough start, but as the tour progresses, Julia’s eccentric side emerges. She enjoys the macabre and is intrigued by some of the stranger stops, though her frustration continues as Chris struggles to give an honest take on the experience.

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who’s stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded “truth warrior” who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his “auditing” police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He’s paranoid, he’s ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he’s very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for “invading his privacy” and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ”spy drone”, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his “truth warrior” life wasn’t wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - “Oshawa”, but is legally required to let the task force know he’s not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he’s the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah’s communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it’ll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he’s been wearing it for 50 years. 

***About Character:**** *A local Oshawa “Shwallywood legend” that has had hundreds of TV and Movie productions use his driveway. A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares “Forrest Gumpian” stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. Obviously no one believes him, which makes him sad. He just just excited to have someone to talk to.

***CHARACTER****:*  Clara “Newswoman”

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***40’s

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Mid-40s, attractive but not delicate, with a confident, professional presence. Simple hair, and a face showing experience rather than youth. Blazer, smart blouse, tailored slacks. Carries a small microphone with the channel logo, Minimal jewelry. 

***About Character: ***Field reporter for a Durham Region news channel. Polished but practical, someone who can run to a chaotic scene without ruining her outfit. Clara is on-site at the Oshawa tourism task force’s Hollywood Tour location, where a body has been discovered. She delivers the story with gravity despite the absurdity of the situation. 

***CHARACTER****:* Chris

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Medium build, white, dark hair. Nerdy, glasses, thrifted clothes or ones he picked up at Costco

***About Character: ***full-time software engineer but would rather talk about his many hobbies and interests like the golden age of cinema, Napoleon, his tropical fish tank, pickleball league and making his girlfriend Julia happy. Chris saw an online ad for the Shwallywood Tour and immediately booked it as he had been looking for a way to propose to his girlfriend, Julia, for months. On the day of, Chris does not immediately react when the tour seems to be taking much longer than anticipated to get to Parkwood as he is a calm and patient person. He only becomes upset when he sees his girlfriend Julia is disappointed in the lackluster activities of the day.

***CHARACTER****:*  Julia

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thin frame, blonde or dark brown hair, A little nerdy, soft goth. 

***About Character: ***Works as a dental assistant. She realized she had a passion for teeth when she did a work placement as a mortician in high school. Julia has been taken on the Shwallywood tour by Chris, to celebrate their anniversary. She initially had very little interest, but Chris insisted on bringing her because she’s a movie buff. The tour is off to a rough start, but as the tour progresses, Julia’s eccentric side emerges. She enjoys the macabre and is intrigued by some of the stranger stops, though her frustration continues as Chris struggles to give an honest take on the experience.

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‘ Habeus Corpus’ by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett’s Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the ﬂat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

**$500 Finders Fee: Have You Been Ghosted By Your Husband Or Wife? (Docu-Series Casting)**

An acclaimed television production company and a major cable network are actively searching for women and men whose spouse has suddenly and mysteriously vanished, without warning, without explanation, and with no way to contact them. If you are still *legally married* but don’t know *where *your spouse is, you don’t have a clear explanation or *“why”* they left, or *how* to reach them, *we want to hear your story for a bold and empowering new series.*

**$500 Referral Fee: **Do You Know Someone? Share their information with us or simply have them tell us you referred them! Finders fee is paid IF referral is selected for production. 

*Selected for series candidates are compensated for taking part as well as receive expert help in tracking down their missing spouse, rebuilding their lives and finding closure. *

**To apply, please email: ****[casting@bodegapictures.com](mailto:casting@bodegapictures.com)****, **or visit: https://abandonedspouseshortapp.castingcrane.com/

items.text:
Liebe Leute! 🇦🇹 

Die WSI Agentur sucht aktuell für folgende Rollen Darsteller!

Alle weiteren Details finden Sie nachfolgend:

Gesuchte Rolle:
-einen Mann (30-45)

Was wird gedreht/produziert?
•  Social Media Content - Kurzvideos (bis ca. 30 Sekunden mit Sprechrollen) und Bilder (div. Motive)

Aufnahmeort: - Ilz/Steiermark/Österreich 
Zeitraum: - 1.10 oder 2.10. (je nach Wetter)

Gage: - Gagenvorstellung des Darstellers für einen halben Drehtag für die ausgeschriebene Rolle

Erfahrung benötigt:
•  Erste Produktionserfahrung von Vorteil
•  Natürlich freuen wir uns auch über Bewerbungen von Laiendarstellern

Die Bewerbung soll bitte unbedingt enthalten:

•  Aktuelle Bilder - min. 3 unterschiedliche Bilder (Polas - Handyfotos)
•  Kurzes Vorstellungsvideo
•  Kontaktdaten: Name, Geburtsdatum, Telefonnummer, Meldeadresse
•  Gagenvorstellung für einen halben Drehtag für die ausgeschriebene Rolle

Wir freuen uns über Ihre Bewerbung an casting@weshootit.com.

Wir bedanken uns und wünschen schöne Grüße aus Graz!

items.text:
Hallo zusammen ,
wir suchen einen **männlichen UGC-Creator**, der in unseren Videos als eine Art **Experten-/Arztfigur** auftritt. Ein Arztkittel oder ähnliches wäre ideal, um den Gesundheitsaspekt zu unterstreichen.

 Wichtig:
* Du brauchst **keine eigenes Haustier** – es geht nur um deine Rolle als Experte.
* Videos sind Talking Head und sehr leicht umsetzbar.
* Script & Briefing bekommst du komplett von uns.

 Produkte stellen wir dir kostenlos zur Verfügung
 Ziel: **eine langfristige Zusammenarbeit mit vielen Projekten und regelmäßigem Content**

Wenn du Interesse hast, melde dich gerne per PN 

Liebe Grüße

Thomas

sharedPost.text:
Szukamy dzieci i rodziców do udziału w planie zdjęciowym 📸

 **Dzieci:**
* 2–3 miesiące
* 5/6 miesięcy 
* 9 miesięcy
* 18 miesięcy (x2)

👨‍👩‍👧 **Szukamy także pary rodziców** (prawdziwi rodzice mile widziani, ale nie wymagane)

.

📅 **Termin:** II połowa października
🕒 **Czas trwania planu:** ok. 3–4 h
💰 **Stawka:** 300 PLN / osoba
💵 **Płatne od razu po planie**
📍 **Miejsce:** Warszawa

Zgłoszenia prosimy wysyłać na 📩 **monika@takamastudio.com**
W treści maila podaj:
* Imię dziecka
* Wiek dziecka + rozmiar ubrania
* Aktualne zdjęcie 

Z wybranymi osobami skontaktujemy się bezpośrednio.

📽️Projekt: Krótki, lekko surrealistyczny film, czarno - biały o aniele w połączeniu że stylem inspirowanym filmografią Wima Wendersa oraz Krzysztofa Kieślowskiego 

📅Data: jeden weekend w październiku, szczegóły do ustalenia 

📍Lokacja: Kraków oraz Skawina

💰Zapłata: 400 zł za dzień (łącznie 800 zł) + koszty za podróż 

Kogo szukamy:

Szukamy młodej (20-30 lat) jasnowłosej dziewczyny pełnej pozytywnej energii i charyzmy.  Otwartej na świat i lubiącej pracować z ludźmi

Wymagania:

- nauczenie się scenariusza

- brak widocznych tatuaży

Co odesłać 

- wizytówkę aktorską

- zdjęcia ( 1 full-body oraz 1 close-up) i/lub profil na social mediach

Zgłoszenia:

Proszę o odesłanie materiałów na maila: ignacyfialek@gmail.com 

Deadline: 3 października

ANIMALS - Schos.             HP bandschos.com
Um die unautorisierte Verbreitung durch Downloads zu verhindern, wurden die auf diesen Plattformen bereitgestellten Songs technisch modifiziert. Dies umfasst das Herausschneiden von Passagen sowie das Einfügen akustischer Urheberrechtshinweise in die Musikstücke.
Riedl Schos keys, songwriting, mix and mastering, producer
Paul Simmons, drums - Mark Corradetti, bass - Chris Mouch, voc 😉

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc)

Summary: Set in the backroom of a dive bar. A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer. Black African, 25-35, Nigerian accent, 5’6”+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £500 for 20 hours (rehearsals & shoot).

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg, powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours.

You will need professional experience playing roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
🎄 CHRISTMAS ELF CASTING – 2025 GROTTO CONTRACT 🎄

(PLEASE BE AWARE WE ARE CASTING FOR MULTIPLE VENUES SO READ CAREFULLY & APPLY ACCORDINGLY) 

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in Barton Grange – and we’re on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

📍 Location: Barton Grange, Brock, Preston, PR3 0BT
📆 Contract: November – December 2025
💸 Rate: £15 per hour — DOUBLE PAY on Christmas Eve

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside Mother Christmas in a beautifully themed setting.

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

• Full availability during weekends and key dates in November/December

• We are ideally looking for team members available for a minimum of 3–5 shifts per week

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

✅ Shift Dates & Times

• Sat, Nov 15 – 9:30 AM to 5:00 PM

• Sun, Nov 16 – 9:00 AM to 4:45 PM

• Sat, Nov 22 – 9:30 AM to 5:00 PM

• Sun, Nov 23 – 9:30 AM to 4:00 PM

(PLEASE BE AWARE WE ARE CASTING FOR MULTIPLE VENUES SO READ CAREFULLY & APPLY ACCORDINGLY) 

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in Barton Grange – and we’re on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

📍 Location: Barton Grange, Brock, Preston, PR3 0BT
📆 Contract: November – December 2025
💸 Rate: £15 per hour — DOUBLE PAY on Christmas Eve

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc)

Summary: Set in the backroom of a dive bar. A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer. Black African, 25-35, Nigerian accent, 5’6”+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £500 for 20 hours (rehearsals & shoot).

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European, 25-35, 5’ 6”+, 85kg-100kg, powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of £300 for 15 hours.

You will need professional experience playing roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com

**📢 DANCE&ARTS IS EXPANDING TO BIRMINGHAM! 🎭💃**

 

Exciting news! You’ve known us in London, and now… we’re bringing the magic to Birmingham too!

 

Dance&Arts is growing, and we're looking for **passionate dance, drama, and arts instructors to join our team in Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young talents, we want to hear from you!

 

✨ We’re hiring for:

✅ Dance (all styles)

✅ Drama

✅ Musical Theatre

✅ Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)

✅ Arts & Crafts

 

💰 Pay: £30 per hour

 

📩 How to Apply: Send your **Enhanced DBS & CV to ****admin@dancearts-uk.com** with your preferred position in the subject line.

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation! 🌟

 

#WeAreExpanding #HiringTeachers #DanceAndArts #TeachingOpportunities #BirminghamJobs #PerformingArts #CreativeEducation

⛱️ HOLIDAY ON THE BUSES 🚌 

The final 'Closer Look' at the Ronald Wolfe auction as there is just 24hrs to go until the auction closes.

Three unique never-before-seen items from the 1973 fan-favourite movie 'Holiday On The Buses.'

Auction ends TOMORROW night from 8pm - still plenty of time to bid!

.
.
.
.
#onthebuses #holidayonthebuses #ronaldwolfe #ronaldchesney #auctioneum #classicbus #bristol #comedy #britishcomedy @onthebusestv @pukkapresenting @britishcomedyguide

items.text:
EXTRAS CALL FOR FEATURE FILM “CLEMONTIME”
📍 Location: Seattle, WA (Ravenna Park)
📅 Shoot Date: October 3rd, 2025
🕒 Time: 2pm-6pm
🎬 Project Type: Independent Feature Film (non-union)
💰 Compensation: unpaid/IMDb Credit/meal provided

Looking For:
Age Range - 18-Late 20s (anyone that can play college students)
Gender - Any gender 

This will be the football park scene. We are looking for men and women to play college students. Come dressed up like you’re in the 80s going to a football game. For the men dress like you’re about to play football and for the women and some men dress like you’re going to one:)

Requirements:
- Must be local to Seattle, WA (unless you can travel, no travel pay)
- Comfortable being on camera for background action
- Must provide own wardrobe, hair, and makeup in 80s style 

To Submit:
Send an email to darecarri2@gmail.com the director with the subject line: “Extras – [Your Name]” and include:
• Full name
• Age & height
• Recent photo (clear, natural, no filters)
• Contact info (phone & email)
• Availability for listed date

This will be a fun opportunity to be part of an indie feature film! Great for experience and networking. Meals and credit provided. We look forward to working with you!

Casting Call - Vancouver BC

Non-Union

Shoot Dates: October (TBD)

Rate: $200 (one day shoot)

Location: Vancouver BC, Kerrisdale.

ROLE:

[Male Lead]

Age: 27-38

Ethnicity: Any

Gender: Man

Callbacks and Rehearsal: Zoom. 

Tone: Grounded and realistic. (e.g Normal People on Prime)

We are seeking a male lead for a one-day location shoot in Kerrisdale for our proof of concept short film. The actor should be comfortable with intimate conversations and improv; open to collaborating during rehearsal to complete the script as we are looking for a very natural and realistic dialogue. 

 TO SUBMIT and RECEIVE AUDITION SIDES: Please send your name, contact info, recent photos or headshots and availability to: [mariajulianakidmoro@gmail.com]

Thanks! Maria and Gabi.

Familiar Faces Casting Call Short Fim Directed by: Daniela Aguirre DATE POSTED: 09-22-2025 POSSIBLE SHOOTING DATES: November 8th OR November 9th, 2025 Rehearsal dates: TBD Location: Chicago, IL
We are committed to diverse, inclusive casting. For every role, please submit qualifiec performers, without regard to disability, race, age, color, national origin, ethnic origin, sexua orientation, gender identity, or any other basis prohibited by law unless otherwise specifically indicated.
Logline : A college undergrad soaring to become a pediatric speech therapist is taunted by ar unexplainable nightmare that has gradually become worse over time.
Roles:
Katalina Desdemona (22) ( Portrayed female Lead) - A senior year college undergrad who grew up in an abusive houschold that impacted her by severely delaying her speech development. With ome help from her ELD teacher (English Language Development) Katalina was able to express herself more growing up and dreams of doing the same for others,
Young Katalina (7-9) (Portrayed female- lead)- Evil spirit who imitates the appearance o Katalina when she was younger. Who's seeking to collect her promised teeth.
Pierre Baker (22) (Portrayed male- supporting)- The loyal best friend of Katalina since 5" grade and who also took interest in studying for child development and literacy. Dedicated and nurturing best friend
If interested, available, or have questions email Daniela Aguirre Send headshots, resumes/reels 

to email: daguirre2@colum.edu

Deadline Date: October 24th. 2025
Compensation: Meal, Copy, Credit

GWC is seeking people to portray 1960s White Upscale Gala Attendees (Ages 30-99) for upcoming A24 horror series MAMAS BOY

To submit, email mamasboy@gwcnyc.com with all the following info using the subject line
“IG Gala”

Full name

Are you a SAG-AFTRA member in good standing (include SAG number) or non-SAG

Phone number

Are you fully available for shoot on 10/9, 10/10 & a TBD fitting?

Please note current height, weight, clothing and shoe sizes*

Please note if you have any tattoos or piercings, and attach a photo

Are you comfortable around atmospheric smoke?

If 21+, are you comfortable smoking a herbal cigarette, if asked? (It’s ok if not)

Men: Are you comfortable being clean shaven for the shoot if needed?

Men & women: Are you comfortable receiving a 1960’s haircut on set, if needed?

Are you local to NJ/NY area?

Confirm you are 18 years or older

Attach current, clear photos (close-up and full body)

This background role is not covered by SAG-AFTRA CBA and subject to a preference of employment provision.

*Height, weight, and clothing sizes are used for costuming purposes only, unless needed for the casting of stand-ins or photodoubles.
Please note, you must be able to present valid identification to fill out a federal I-9 form and be paid.

#extras #gala #1960 #elegant #a24

Palmera Entertainment Job Offer 🩷

 JOB: SINGERS 🎤  & DANCERS 🕺

🇬🇧UK CITIZENS ARE WELCOME! 🇬🇧

🌞 – Male & female, Dancers & Singers Under the Greek Sun! 🇬🇷🕺🎤

(EU citizens & non-EU residents with a valid EU residence permit welcome)

This is your last chance to land a paid summer job in paradise for 2 Months !
Palmera Entertainment is hiring for the final dancer and singer positions at 5★ resorts in the beautiful Greek Islands.
If you love the stage, sun, and sea – this job is for you.
🎭 Available Roles:
 • Dancer / performer 
 • Singer / Performer
📍 Location: 5★ Hotels – Greek Islands
📅 Contract Dates: August 1st – October 31st, 2025
📄 Swiss employment contract
💶 Net Salary: €900-1200€ /month + commissions ( depends on positions& experiences)
🎬 See what we do🎭
👉 Watch our showreel : https://youtu.be/9PdbLO--GX4?si=W8fKURLEWPjE9bCG 
✅ We Offer:
 • 🏡 Free accommodation
 • 🍽️ Full board (3 meals/day) + drinks included in the main restaurant 
 • 🚖 Free transfer from airport to hotel
 • 📶 Free internet & laundry service 
 • 🧥 Free uniforms
 • 🎓 Free rehearsals and show training
 • 🧳 €200-300€ travel bonus (paid at contract end)
 • 🛡️ Full insurance (accident, pension, social)
 • 💰 Extra bonuses for merchandising promo
 • ☀️ An unforgettable summer experience
🕒 Typical Workday (6~8 hrs)
 • 🎭 4-5 performances/week, 1 hour per show
 • 🎬 Rehearsals: As needed (usually midday)
Schedules can vary slightly by hotel and concept – flexibility is key.
🌍 You Need To Be:
 • An EU citizen 
 • Energetic, outgoing, team-oriented
 • Experienced or passionate about dance, singing, or performing
 Nn• Confident engaging with international hotel guests
 • Fully available from September  to October 2025

Instagram: palmera_entertainment
TikTok: palmera_entertainment

💬 Don’t miss your chance and shine with Palmera  !☀️🎶🌴 apply now @ : adriano@palmera-agency.com

I’m thrilled to officially announce that casting is underway for my short film The Spaces Between! 🎬 The project is coming to life, and I can’t wait to share this story with all of you.

Even more exciting — our Indiegogo campaign is now live! 🚀 This is your chance to be part of the journey from the very beginning. Every contribution, big or small, helps us bring this vision to the screen — from supporting our amazing cast and crew to making sure every frame tells the story it deserves.

👉 [https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/the-spaces-between--2#/]

PS. CASTING HAD CLOSED 

Thank you for all the encouragement so far. I’m beyond grateful for your support, and I can’t wait to keep you updated as we move forward. Let’s make The Spaces Between a reality together! 💜

items.text:
Casting Call ✨✨✨✨

Hi! My name is Madeleine Bloore. I’m a Writer-Director currently developing my own short film. I’m fortunate to be working with an incredibly talented team of filmmakers who are just as passionate as I am about bringing this story to life.

‘The Lines We Crossed’ is a raw and tender story of found family, the messiness of healing, and the unexpected power of being seen. Three lives, stitched together by loneliness, come alive in the light of connection - and in that light, hope can take root where none was meant to grow.

We are now on the lookout for our secondary characters: The parents 👀

Mrs. Kane is dramatic, flirty, and unapologetically over-the-top, with a flair for gossip and a love of all things a little chavvy. While she loves both of her children, her eldest, Cody, is clearly the favorite - her pride and joy - often leaving Keira to fend for herself. Mrs. Kane desperately clings to Cody’s success, seeing it as her ticket to status and financial security.

• Female
• 30-55 years
• White/Caucasian
• London Accent

📍Location: London
💰 Payment: Unpaid
✨ Great opportunity for actors looking to gain experience, showreel material, and festival exposure.

🫵 Are you our Mrs. Kane? 🫵

Auditions are open now 🎬
Contact IG: @lines_we_crossed_film

Director's Vision:
With the retro soul of ‘The Breakfast Club’ blended with the early warmth of ‘Friends’, this film reshapes nostalgia into a heartfelt tale of friendship, human connection, and the enduring promise of hope.

As the writer and director, my vision for this film is to transport audiences into the nostalgic energy of the 80s - a vibrant, colorful, and effortlessly cool era - while keeping it deeply relatable for today’s teenagers and young adults. At its heart, this story reflects the universal struggles of growing up: finding our place, defining who we are, and learning who we can trust.

I want this film to remind us that life is full of unexpected opportunities, and that we are not bound to what we start out with. The future belongs to us - we just have to be brave enough to reach for it.

We can’t wait to hear from you 😉

Contact IG: @lines_we_crossed_film

Director's Vision:
With the retro soul of ‘The Breakfast Club’ blended with the early warmth of ‘Friends’, this film reshapes nostalgia into a heartfelt tale of friendship, human connection, and the enduring promise of hope.

As the writer and director, my vision for this film is to transport audiences into the nostalgic energy of the 80s - a vibrant, colorful, and effortlessly cool era - while keeping it deeply relatable for today’s teenagers and young adults. At its heart, this story reflects the universal struggles of growing up: finding our place, defining who we are, and learning who we can trust.

I want this film to remind us that life is full of unexpected opportunities, and that we are not bound to what we start out with. The future belongs to us - we just have to be brave enough to reach for it.

We can’t wait to hear from you 😉

**🎬 CASTING DO TELEDYSKU – PŁATNE 🎬**

**Warszawa**

Poszukujemy osób z doświadczeniem aktorskim lub modelingowym do udziału w teledysku młodego i bardzo utalentowanego wykonawcy. Projekt ma charakter surrealistyczny i konceptualny.

📅** Termin realizacji: 05.10 (niedziela), godz. 14:00 – ok. 02:00** (część nocy)

💰 **Projekt płatny**

👉** Poszukiwane role:**

**1. Dziadek** – mężczyzna w wieku 50–75 lat

**2. Mężczyzna** – w wieku 30–45 lat

📩 Zgłoszenia prosimy przesyłać na adres: **casting.kamilaboichenko@gmail.com**

W tytule maila należy wpisać: **ROLA – TELEDYSK – Imię i Nazwisko**

**Do zgłoszenia należy dołączyć:**

1. Imię i nazwisko + wiek

2. Miasto zamieszkania

3. Aktualne zdjęcia (portret + sylwetka)

4. Informację o doświadczeniu + wizytówkę lub showreel (jeśli jest)

5. Wymiary, rozmiar ubrań i butów

6. Dane kontaktowe: nr telefonu i adres e-mail

Zapraszam do udziału w wyjątkowym projekcie – czekamy na Wasze zgłoszenia!

Pozdrawiam serdecznie,

Reżyserka castingu 

Kamila Boichenko

🎭🎶 CASTINGI DO MUSICALU „S!X” WE WROCŁAWSKIM TEATRZE DIALOGU! 🎶🎭

Już w kwietniu 2026 roku odbędzie się trzecia polska premiera światowego hitu – musicalu „S!X” autorstwa Toby’ego Marlowa i Lucy Moss, w reżyserii Michała Jagodzińskiego. 🔥

👉 Poszukujemy:
✨ Aktorek musicalowych – pełnoletnich, mieszkających na Dolnym Śląsku, studentek i absolwentek szkół aktorskich oraz muzycznych, związanych ze sceną musicalową.
✨ Gitarzystki i basistki – instrumentalistek z doświadczeniem scenicznym, najlepiej z obszaru muzyki teatralnej lub koncertowej.

📅 Terminy:
Aktorki musicalowe – casting wieloetapowy: zgłoszenia do 12 października 2025, godz. 23:59.
Gitarzystka i basistka –  wyłącznie jeden etap: zgłoszenia również do 12 października 2025, godz. 23:59.

📩 Zgłoszenia przyjmujemy mailowo na adres: six@teatr-dialogu.pl

W tytule maila: „Imię i nazwisko – Postać/Instrument – SIX”.

Szczegóły, wymagania oraz zakresy wokalne znajdziecie w pełnych ogłoszeniach ➡️ teatr-dialogu.pl/castingi/

Dołącz do zespołu, który stworzy trzecią polską premierę tego wyjątkowego musicalu! 💜👑🎤

**Statistinnen gesucht für Kinodokumentarfilm**

Für einen szenischen Kinodokumentarfilm zum Thema „Liebe im Alter“ (Koproduktion mit dem ZDF) suchen wir kurzfristig Statistinnen.
Der Dreh findet morgen, Freitag 25.09., zwischen 16:00 und 18:00 Uhr im Museum in Bonn statt.

Bitte beachten Sie, dass lediglich eine kleine Aufwandsentschädigung (20 € die Stunde) gezahlt werden kann.

Wir freuen uns über Ihr Interesse und eine kurze Rückmeldung.

Hier unsere Website zu der Produktion:
[https://solange-es-nicht-aufhoert.de/](https://solange-es-nicht-aufhoert.de/)

items.text:
** CASTING-AUFRUF – UGC-Videodreh für Immobilienprojekt in Hamburg // 30.09.2025**

 **Drehort:** Hamburg 

 **Drehtag:** Dienstag, 30. September 2025 – Start: 10:00 Uhr

 **Dauer:** ca. 4–5 Stunden (halber Drehtag)

 **Honorar:** 500 € Pauschalgage
** Was wir drehen:**

Für unseren Kunden – ein Immobilienunternehmen aus Hamburg – produzieren wir **15 kurze UGC-Videos** (User Generated Content), die für **Social Media & Online-Ads** eingesetzt werden.

Die Clips bestehen aus **authentischen Monologen**, die direkt in die Kamera gesprochen werden: **klar, sympathisch, ruhig und professionell**.
* Skriptlänge: 40–60 Sekunden pro Clip
* Teleprompter ist vor Ort (kein Auswendiglernen nötig)
* Fokus: **seriöse, glaubwürdige Darstellung**
** Wen wir suchen:**

 **1 Schauspieler (männlich)**
* Alter: 25–35 Jahre
* Look: gepflegt, urban, authentisch-professionell (z. B. „Young Professional“-Vibe – denkbar wären Start-up-Gründer, Immobilienberater, Creator mit Vertrauensausstrahlung)
* Sprache: Hochdeutsch, **klare Artikulation** und sichere Präsenz vor der Kamera
* Erfahrung mit Social Media Ads ist ein Plus, aber **keine Voraussetzung**
** Über uns:**

Wir sind die **IMMO 4.0 GmbH**, ein Performance-Marketing-Unternehmen aus Heidelberg.

Unser Schwerpunkt: **Marketingkampagnen für Immobilienvertriebe, Bauträger und Kapitalanlagen im gesamten DACH-Raum**.

MOVIETIME KW 40/2025

Ein Serienklassiker verabschiedet sich, Remake eines Kinderbuchklassikers und Kinofeeling für die Swifties

Die aktuelle Kalenderwoche hat es in sich, zunächst das Grande Finale von DOWNTOWN ABBEY (Stadtkino Horn) sowie fast 40 Jahre danach die Neuverfilmung von Michael Endes MOMO (Babylon Kino Horn,  Stadtkinocenter Laa und Filmbühne Waidhofen).

Ende September startete das Langfilmdebüt von Marie Luise Lehner in den Lichtspielhäusern. Das Ergebnis unseres Gespräches hören Sie in der Sendung.

Musikalisch gedenken wir der kürzlich verstorbenen Claudia Cardinale. 

Sarah Fuchs führt sie durch das nun wöchentliche Filmmagazin und sagt Ihnen auch, für welchen Film sich der Kinobesuch lohnt.

Mittwoch 01.10.2025 von 18 - 19 h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

🚨 CASTING CALL: BUSINESS OWNERS 🚨 
PLEASE KINDLY SHARE FOR ME 🙌🏼

I’m currently casting for an exciting QuickBooks project featuring UK-based entrepreneurs and business owners.

We’re especially keen to hear from those with businesses turning over £1 million+ per year, but we also welcome passionate founders operating at any level — if your business has a brilliant story, we want to hear it.

🎥 This is a paid opportunity to feature in YouTube gameshow-style content — a fun and engaging way to promote your business to a wide audience.

👉 Know someone? Tag them here.
📩 Want to apply? Email me at: casper@casperblackcasting.com

Let’s shine a light on the UK’s most inspiring businesses 🔥

We are seeking enthusiastic actresses for an upcoming independent zombie movie. This project blends horror, suspense, and dark humor. Shooting dates are TBD and will take place in the local area.

Who we are looking for? 

Women aged 16-28 who have a passion for horror! We have leading roles that need to be filled and want young up and coming talent to take that spotlight! 

WE ARE SEARCHING FOR TONS OF NEW TALENT AND ENCOURAGE ALL WOMAN OF ALL BACKGROUNDS TO APPLY. WE DEDICATE OUR PROCESS INTO INVOLVING AND UPLIFITING THOSE WHO MAY FACE BARRIERS. (If you need accommodations please let us know)

To be considered, please leave your contact info in the link below and our team will be in contact shortly. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScVk2oj-ptgpQGc2fkTnoIsQNqpjmvULZ5VqiLGJStwHGN3rQ/viewform?fbclid=IwQ0xDSwKd7RFleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABHm_-bBN6sRA6a7BHOaFJxrigOEUykOBehWrZ6bIpMHvlcUu6F8Uf4bF1DUIU_aem_cMRRZUQ6WYUZMnP7j7yodA

CASTING CALL for a SHORT we are producing in November.

COLD FEET

A dark comedy --- On his wedding day, Thomas tries to weasel his way out of lifetime commitment. But the universe has other plans for him.

Casting for

Thomas - The groom. A go-with-the-flow guy who realises too late that getting married is not what he wants.

Elliott - The best man who tries to set his friend on the right path.

Jane - An intense bride, who refuses to see the ugly truth about the supposed love of her life.

Must be willing to travel to Beaconsfield, Buckinghamshire (HP9).

Filming dates tentatively set for November 29-30, 2025.

This is a paid opportunity. Short film rates.

Please fill out this form to register your interest! https://forms.gle/U8PgSfkotmqSa9M16

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR PLAY IN LONDON:

I'm casting four roles (3 female/ 1 male) for a showcase reading of my new play 'The Beat of the Bronzewing' at the Hen & Chickens Theatre in Islington, London on November 12th. 

The Beat of the Bronzewing was longlisted for the Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025 and focuses on three women in remote tropical Australia, desperate to turn their lives around yet paralysed by fear. It explores how their insecurities and the wild landscape magnify their loneliness and isolation, setting them on a course of self-destruction as they increasingly turn on each other. 

Apply via the Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR5Hu3UGD1qZxdMIWR2d_80GBkptrNYjvmQKWCmydP--a9Hs-hLLyq9GDFqZlA_aem_Tn4v_Jq0QGNGHkakZGOTFw)). 

Know someone who might be interested? Please spread the word!

 

Important info:  

| Rehearsals on November 9th (10am-6pm) and November 12th (2:30-7pm)

| In-person auditions on October 8th (12-5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre in Angel, Islington following a selection (let us know if you need an alternative) 

| Volunteer opportunity - all actors will be given £50 pounds for expenses

| Apply via Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fd98EEgkgK0%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR6STL3lXt8cdBCGpSYrv5XvpSHW_IA3JoKT1r83vfoq93QMm80Vsj_31_s09Q_aem_cSh3Con8n2nt4AWPGVxuRQ&h=AT3UxWehtfMsSwB5REWXCX3UHOR-IbCtMgXw11AVLk6tzDWjrVusQvMal4tBpcgnFYk6zyQaOjGLupowpQG2C_2Lnir-BGUKBI9MH_CMk-pF1FA-OIIZsoxFFo2bSplp5WYnUXM019O0AA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3ZSFem3LQLGHpnYQQix_aB1OTC-II_z6ULdAtsi-abLh1hVZ6JVCHBA2u98UrsMqLeuH-VMmJqsPkp102wldtR3ternY9MXCYToG6v5AsMe_3MJvv4-JL2oxzyNfi1_K7uf8f1E10-EvfRY4j_OFAP6nnjb1-iHjbe3u5HTKwR)) - thank you!

items.text:
Casting Call

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-35 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 14th of October day time in Croydon, London, next to Waddon station. 

Salary will be £25 for the actor after filming, plus if actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me:

I am producer and one of the directors of the film. My name: Ieva Kondrataviciute 
Email: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com
Contact WhatsApp: +44 7548710376

items.text:
Vi er et ambitiøst crew fra Københavns film & fotoskole og søger mandlige statister til vores midtvejsproduktion “KAMMERATER”

Vi filmer imorgen den 1. fra (09-17) og Torsdag den 2. fra (12-17), man behøves ikke kunne være der hele tiden. Vi er fleksible. 

(I kan læse detaljer om filmen i det vedlæggende billede)

Vi søger udseendemæssigt i alderen 19-27 år, men tøv ikke med at skrive, selvom det ikke matcher jeres alder! Man behøver derudover heller ikke kunne være der begge dage, få timer kan stadig bruges!

I vil selvfølgelig blive krediteret i filmen og få en mega fed oplevelse af at være på kortfilm’s set!

Skriv til mig på mit nr. 21259241, til den vedlagte mail eller her på opslaget hvis det kunne have interesse!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambitiøse og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en række skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske fætter hjælper ham med at flytte, må han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud – men om at turde definere sine egne grænser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke særlig bemærkelsesværdig
* har svært ved at sætte grænser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 år
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* KØN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ulønnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail på sara774g@gmail.com med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi glæder os til at høre fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

"Roughly Speaking" is a  play extremely near and dear to my heart. Please pre-order your copy. They're only $10.95 and the pre-sale numbers really help it get on shelves in some important places. If you're the type of person who likes to buy plays or are looking for a new monologue or want to support me and my work, I'd super appreciate it. It won't be on Amazon, but I'm hoping it will be on shelves. Please please please request it at bookstores. I am feeling all the feelings today. My heart is full. 

Order here: https://next-stage-press.myshopify.com/products/roughly-speaking-by-shara-ashley-zeiger

items.text:
CASTING CALL / PAID / Non-Union / Photography

Looking for five diverse talents for a two-day photography project in showcasing community services and programs. Professional photo shoot requiring natural, authentic interactions representing local residents.

Desired Attributes:

  • Non-union

  • Mixed ages and ethnicities to represent community diversity

  • Senior (Age 65+)

  • Young students (Age 18-22)

  • Young professionals (Age 30-40)

  • Available October 8-9 (subject to change) in Lower Mainland

  • Comfortable with professional photography environment

  • Natural, approachable appearance

Usage:

  • Municipal marketing and promotional materials in Canada

  • Perpetual

Budget:

  • $700 / person / day

Apply @ go.opencast.ca/casting/CSO

Questions? info@opencast.ca

items.text:
Casting for: Queer actresses, episodic series leads types, early 20's.

Holding open auditions for several new queer episodic series we are working on, looking for actresses who can play women who are just about to meet/are at the start of same-sex dating and relationships.

Open ethnicity, early 20's look, attractive, in shape. Non-union. Paid (TBD). Actors do not actually need to be queer, just be able to play the role.

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be in Winter 2025/2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.
