items.text:
**SERIAL HISTORYCZNY - ŁÓDŹ - 04.10**

Na plan serialu kryminalnego szukamy statystów oraz epizodysty na plan 04.10:
* **Statyści i epizodysta: **mężczyźni w wieku ok. 30-50 lat - naturalny wygląd, bez widocznych tatuaży, ogoleni i bez nowoczesnych fryzur; rozmiar max. L, 170-180 cm wzrostu. 

**Stawka: **120 zł - statyści; 300 zł - epizodysta.

**Gdzie: **Łódź.

**Kiedy: **04.10.

*Dojazd we własnym zakresie.

*Prosimy o zgłoszenia z aktualnymi zdjęciami.

**Zgłoszenia **proszę wysyłać na adres: wawa.statysci@gmail.com

podając: imię i nazwisko, wiek, numer kontaktowy, AKTUALNE zdjęcia, a w przypadku epizodystów - dodatkowo wizytówka.

Proszę podać informację**, czy zgłaszasz się na statystowanie, epizod czy na jedno i drugie.** W tytule: "Łódź - 04.10".

items.text:
Warszawa! 
Do serialu Gliniarze poszukujemy epizodystów: 
1.           Siostra Pawłowskiej (50) – Starsza siostra ofiary, zatroskana i zaniepokojona. Sweter i sukienka, scena płaczu.  (3,4)  2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
2.           Dominik „Dziki” Jaworski (24) – Świetnie jeździ na hulajnodze elektrycznej. Prawie wszystkie sceny w kasku, mało mówi. Diler, paser i przestępca. Kask, kurtka i spodnie z ochraniaczami. (1,2,16,17,18,18A,18B,23,24) AKTOR – JEŹDZI NA HULAJNODZE, proszę o informację o ukończonej szkole aktorskiej
Data: 13 i 14 października
Stawka: 1200 zł netto za całość
 
3.           Mikołaj Bielecki (45) – Były partner ofiary, diler z długami. Groził jej, że ją pobije w wyniku kłótni o pieniądze. (6-OFF,7,8) 2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
4.           Diler (37) – Mężczyzna, który sprzedawał Białowąsowi narkotyki do dalszego handlu. Większy, silniejszy, podejrzany. Nie budzi zaufania, agresywny, w dresie, ale na bogato (modna torebeczka, jednoczęściowy dres) (6-OFF,7)  2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
5.           Pani Rojek (59) – Babcia Kartona, widzi w nim niewinnego wnuczka. Stara się go sama wychować, ale nie jest łatwo na własnej emeryturze. Spódnica i sweter (11)  2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
6.           Hubert „Karton” Rojek (18) – Problematyczny nastolatek, zajarany półświatkiem. Też kupił sobie e-hulajnogę, aby kraść ludziom telefony na ulicy. Jest jednak zagubiony i sfrustrowany, że nie ma w życiu tak łatwo jak inni nastolatkowie z drogimi smartfonami. Szeroki dżinsy, luźna bluza, modna fryzura – (13,14) 1 PLAN
Data: 13 i 17  października
Stawka: 700 zł netto
 
7.           Kolega Kartona (20) – Pseudo spec od telefonów, ale tak naprawdę zwykły nastolatek, który chciałbyć inżynierem z youtube’a. Dżinsy i koszulka. (13) 2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
8.           Zbychu „Ślepy” Wasiak (53) – Właściciel szemranego lombardu, który sprzedaj kradzione rzeczy. Typ sprzedawcy naciągacza, który słodzi w ofercie, a po wszystkim jest chamski i niemiły. Spodnie, rozpięta koszula i t-shirt (16,17,20,21) SPECJALNA
Data: 14 października
Stawka: 450 zł netto
 
 
9.           Michalina Pawłowska (47) – Kobieta, która zostaje potrącona przez mężczyznę w hulajnodze. Ma przemocowego ex, ale sama z normalnego świata.  (1,2)  2 PLAN
Data: 13 października
Stawka: 250 zł netto
 
10.       Klient (27) podejrzliwy klient w lombardzie, zna rynek i aktualne ceny (16) EPIZOD
Data: 14 października
Stawka: 200 zł netto
 
·       Mundurowy 1 – (3,5) EPIZOD
 
 
Chętne osoby zapraszam do wysyłania zgłoszeń na adres: casting.outset@interia.pl
W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.
W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:
1.           Wiek/wzrost/waga
2.           Krótki opis doświadczenia
3.           Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki castingowe
4.           Aktualne zdjęcie
5.           Informacje o posiadanym i czynnym prawie jazdy lub jego braku
Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu/noclegu

items.text:
2 Spots Left!! 

The On Camera Experience, co-taught by actor Rob Kerkovitch (CSI New Orleans) and Sylvia Gregory, CSA.

6 Classes
October 7th - November 11th 
Tuesdays, 6:30 PM until roughly 9:30 PM
$475 per person (that’s only $80 per class!)
Class Outline
Class One: Getting to know each other, on camera terms and techniques
Class Two: Commercials
Class Three: Comedy
Class Four: Drama
Class Five: Video Games
Class Six: “On Set” - a professional camera op will be filming this class. 
Classes will be a mix of on-camera acting technique and scene study with some acting feedback. All raw footage will be filmed and shared with the students. 
Must join by Wednesday, October 1st.  SPACE IS LIMITED!! To reserve a spot, please contact Sylvia at sylvia@sylviagregorycasting.com
Hope you can be a part of it!

items.title: 2 Spots Left!!

items.text:
“Scrooge! (Abbreviated Version)” 

Book, Music and Lyrics by Leslie Bricusse

From A Christmas Carol by Charles Dickens

A one-hour adaptation of the crowd-pleasing holiday musical!

In 1970, renowned writer/composer/lyricist Leslie Bricusse adapted the classic Charles Dickens tale A Christmas Carol into the hit screen musical Scrooge! 

A charming stage musical, Scrooge! 

Lyons Community Theatre

Auditions: Will be held at Planet Bluegrass Lab Building(Directions), on Friday, Oct 3rd, 5-7pm; Sunday, Oct 5th,  1-3pm and Monday, Oct 6th, 5-7pm  (If none of these days or times work for you, please contact georgi.pollard@gmail.com by Sunday, Oct 5th @12pm

Performance dates:

Friday, December 12th, 2025 @7pm 

Saturday, December 13th, 2025 @2pm & 7pm

Sunday, December 14th, 2025 @2pm 

@Planet Bluegrass Wildflower Pavillion 

All auditioners  will be asked to sing 16 measures from the musical or a verse from a familiar holiday song.

We will dance a few moves and those wanting a speaking role will read from the script. Everyone is encouraged to show off your English accent!  Although not necessary, you are welcome to bring a prepared song to share.  We will have an accompanist.

Roles are Non-Union | Unpaid

LCT encourages actors of all races, ethnicities, genders, ages, and abilities all ages to audition, welcoming performers from all backgrounds.

Performers may come on any one of the days or you may sign up using the Signup Genius link

Link to Sign up for an Audition Slot:

SIGN UP LINK

https://www.signupgenius.com/go/70A0A4BA4A723ABFE3-58313489-scrooge#/

Title: With the Skin

Genre: Psychological thriller

Logline: An infantilized woman sheltered by her overprotective mother is drawn to the outside world by a budding attraction to her charismatic neighbor. She must choose between the safety of the life she knew and the allure of the unknown.

Roles: 

**Ines** (female, 20s) *An infantilized woman beginning to venture from her protected bubble.*

**Evelyn** (female, 40s) *An overprotective mother, desperately trying to maintain her daughter’s innocence.*

**Wendy** (female, 20s) *A nosy drifter who moves in next door, always looking for excitement.*

**Johnny** (male, early 30s) *A pushy musician who lives to party.*

Production Type: CU Denver Junior Thesis student film

Contact Information: sarojadmanickam@gmail.com, sign up for in-person auditions or submit self tapes at [https://forms.gle/12DzeBY1Q7hK21St6](https://forms.gle/12DzeBY1Q7hK21St6)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: 

Evelyn $125/day

Ines $100/day

Wendy and Johnny will be unpaid

Food and transportation will be provided for all roles 

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: There will be in-person auditions at the Auraria Campus Library on October 2nd and October 3rd. Time slots are available on the QR code questionnaire.

Shooting Schedule: November 7th-9th (subject to slight changes) & a table read in mid-October

Filming Location: Primarily Castle Rock, CO - transportation can be arranged and provided

Project Description: This film contains sensitive material and depictions of sexual assault, cannibalism, and both emotional and physical abuse. These will be emotionally demanding roles, so make sure that you are comfortable and able to commit.

Hey everyone

Currently casting roles for an upcoming dark comedy/horror short film

It is to be filmed in Northern/Central NJ on October 10th & 11th. We have an extremely talented crew and a great script. Here are the two roles we need to fill:

**Matt** (Young male, 20s-30): on the sarcastic side, emotive, physically comedic, able to display fear and be funny simultaneously, slightly over-the-top to play off shock factor/dark comedy bits

**Ron** (Young male, 20s-30): sincere, thoughtful, introspective, innocent. plays it straight to contrast the hyperbole around him

Please DM me if you are interested along with your acting reel. **Must be available both days!**

This is a **volunteer** gig for imdb credit, experience, and the chance to collaborate on a high quality production that will circuit quite a few festivals!

items.text:
**CASTING NOTICE**

Non-Equity Call; $35.00 performance rate

*Trinity Theatre Company is seeking actors to join our Storytime Troupe, a year-round program that tours libraries around San Diego. These positions are on-going, as needed. Performers should generally be available weekdays during the day. At each performance, ****two ****actors of the troupe will be scheduled. Performances are typically 75 minutes, including setup and tear down (required of Troupe performers). Storytime Coordinator: ****Marcy Ledvinka. ****Artistic Director: ****Sean Boyd****.*

**Only Self-taped Auditions **are being accepted. *All submissions* *must be emailed to **[marcy@trinityttc.org](mailto:casting@trinityttc.org)** by 5:00 PM on October 3, 2025.*

****Actors of all ethnicities, race, age, and gender are encouraged to apply****

To submit, email [marcy@trinityttc.org](mailto:casting@trinityttc.org). Include:

1) Your name

2) Your email & phone number

3) Digital copy of your headshot and resume

4) General availability, including daytime and weekend availability

5) A recording of you performing the side below

***If you do not receive a response confirming materials have been collected within 48 hours, please resend your information.***

Other essential duties and requirements of Storytime Actors:
* Must pass Background Checks and LiveScan certification
* Audience participation with children, including post-show craft supervision
* May be asked to serve as “Coordinator” (paid as performer)
* Set-up and Take Down of Trinity approved set, costumes, and props
* Maintenance of Storytime Marketing Kit
* Submit timely performance reports
* Attendance at Monthly Storytime Meeting (scheduled around actor availability, though often 4th Sunday at 10a OR Saturday at 6p)
* Performances are county-wide. Reliable transportation is required (public transit, personal car, other modes are all acceptable).

**SIDE TO RECORD:**

**KNACK. **Well, that’s everyone on our farm! Maybe we can spend some more time all

together. Can I show you my garden? *(*INTERACTION MOMENT*)* I have so much I could

show you! I have recently just started growing daisies! Ooh! I am so excited. I know exactly

what I want to show you first—(Knack notices a seed on the ground and picks it up.) What is

this? Sorry everyone...I did not put this here. What do you think this is? (*INTERACTION

MOMENT*) Wait! I have seen this before. It’s...it’s a seed of wheat! Wow! If we plant the seed,

we could make fresh bread! Oh yum! (Beat.) But I’ve never planted anything like this before.

You know...I think I want some help planting this seed of wheat. Let’s go ask Don the Dog!

items.text:
Er du en lille pige som altid har ønsket at stå foran et kamera? 

Til kortfilmen “Dukkebarn” søger vi en pige med en ben protese eller arm protese til rollen som AURA. 

Lidt om filmen: 
“Dukkebarn udforsker den skrøbelige grænse mellem fantasi og virkelighed gennem øjnene på Aura. Hendes fascination til dukker bliver en måde at bearbejde hendes egen smertelige virkelighed og hendes forhold til sin krop. Gennem leg, skabelse og destruktion konfronteres hun med sine dybeste frugter og længsler. 

Alder: I mellem 6-12 år. 

Vi filmer i Århus d. 16-18 Januar 2026. Jobbet vil være lønnet, samt forplejning og transport. Søg gerne lige meget hvor i landet du bor. Vi ser gerne så mange som muligt;) 

Skriv til @Rirh.prod@gmail.com med emnet “CASTING -DUKKEBARN”. Skrive gerne lidt om dig selv, samt er billede og evt erfaring. 

Hvis du er gået videre til casting, eller fået rollen vil du få svar inden 10 Januar. 

Jeg glæder mig til at høre fra jer. 

Mvh Rebecca Renner Hansen - Dukkebarn film

sharedPost.text:
🎭 Bliv en del af vores escape room-univers!🔐

Elsker du at spille skuespil, skabe mindeværdige oplevelser og få folk til at grine? Så har vi drømmejobbet til dig!

Hos Midgaard Event søger vi nye kollegaer til vores levende escape rooms i København. Som gamemaster bliver du en vigtig del af oplevelsen, både som vært og som en del af spillets fortælling.

🧩 Vi tilbyder:
• Løn på 130-150 kr./timen + salgsbonusser
• Arbejde primært torsdag til lørdag
• En sjov, social og kreativ arbejdsplads
• Mulighed for ansvar og udvikling

🎭 Dine opgaver:
• Skabe en mindeværdig og underholdende oplevelse som både vært og fortæller
• Sikre spillets flow og koordinere bag kulisserne i tæt samarbejde med kollegaer
• Klargøre rum, genskabe stemningen og holde driften skarp hele dagen

🎯 Lyder det som noget for dig, eller kender du den rette?
Så send en ansøgning og CV til hello@escaperoom.dk
Det behøver ikke være traditionelt, vi elsker, når personlighed og kreativitet skinner igennem. ✨

Vi glæder os til at høre fra dig!

items.title: (no title)

items.text:
Hi there!

I'm the owner of Clutch Casting, a casting company specialising in short form projects & stills.

We're currently casting a Photography Project for Photographer Poppy Thorpe.

We are looking to meet real Granddaughters and their maternal Grandmothers who share a deep bond and would like an opportunity to encapsulate their unique relationship.

It will be a celebration of love and friendship, female strength and resilience, spotlighting beauty and the wisdom to be found in older women, especially Grandmothers.

Diversity across ethnicity, age, body types and sexuality is important in this project. The photographer is interested to show how being a Grandmother can vary across cultural backgrounds.

Details:

This is a passion project and therefore unpaid. Each participant will be given a print of the final photograph/s. 

Participants can be based anywhere in the UK/Europe & the photographer will travel to your location to shoot around your schedule from October-December.

The photographs will not be used commercially, for advertising or marketing. They are solely for the purposes of this personal artistic project.

For more information & how to apply, please see the link below:

[https://form.jotform.com/Casting_Clutch/cast-wanted-for-photography-project](https://form.jotform.com/Casting_Clutch/cast-wanted-for-photography-project)

Thank you!

Laura @ Clutch Casting 

[https://www.instagram.com/clutchcasting/](https://www.instagram.com/clutchcasting/)

Ready Set Recycle now operating globally. Check out some great items being offered for free in the United Kingdom.  
ReadySetRecycle.com is a web-based company that recycles anything and everything from the show business industry. We offer a full line of services including Fixed Price Sales and Auctions. Or for individual items just create an account and post them yourself completely free of charge, just like on Craigs List. We have almost 120,000 followers on our socials where we get millions of views! Since 2021 we have run sales for 57 shows and kept thousands of tons of sets, props, costumes and materials out of landfill. Let us help you make money instead of spending money on dumpsters. [https://www.readysetrecycle.com/advert/white-melamine-desk-bar-dj-booth/](https://www.readysetrecycle.com/advert/white-melamine-desk-bar-dj-booth/)
